            <div type="prose">
                <head type="title">150. "There is a solemn silence on the scene" Witness</head>
                <p>150. &#x201C;There is a solemn silence on the scene,&#x201D; <date when="1831-12">December 1831</date> to <date when="1832-01">January 1832</date>, 
                    MS VIII. Previously unpublished.</p>
                
                <p>See no. 148 for dating.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem">
                <head type="title">There is a solemn silence on the scene</head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>There is a solemn silence on the scene</l>
                    <l>Scarce broken by the mountain breezes sigh</l>
                    <l>From <subst><del>???????</del><add>deep ravine</add></subst><del>hold</del> come forth &#x0026; sailing by<!--check deletion--></l>
                    <l>The distant ocean rolling on serene</l>
                    <l>Its smiling waters gilded by the beam</l>
                    <l>That glows upon the bosom of the tide</l>
                    <l>Boundless and mighty as its <subst><del>ripples</del><add>billows</add></subst> ride</l>
                    <l>Scattered with gold by the departing <subst><del>beam</del><add>gleam</add></subst></l>
                    <l><subst><del>Rolling their</del><add>In thousand</add></subst> little circles <subst><del>to the shore</del><add>as they sweep</add></subst></l>
                    <l>To roll them on its sands to break and die <!--'and' here looks more like 'tand'?--></l>
                    <l>The sun that sinks <subst><del>below them hath ???</del><add>to ocean pillowed sleep</add></subst> <!--check deletion--></l>
                    <l><subst><del>????? of a ???? sky</del><add>Bids slowly and adieu to earth and sky</add></subst><!--Here deletes an entire line of which I'm unsure--></l>
                    <l>The dews of evening this departure weep <!--Here deletes TWO entire lines of which I'm unsure, one above and one below--></l>
                    <l>And night her head sinks down upon the deep</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
            <div type="prose">
                <p>L. 12, 13 written above heavily canceled lines.</p>
            </div> 
